# Core Principles

- Prefer existing patterns — no new frameworks or styles without explicit approval
- Minimize change surface — touch only what is necessary
- When uncertain, state assumptions explicitly and ask before proceeding
- No secrets, PII, or credentials in code or commits
- For non-trivial changes, pause and consider a more elegant approach; skip for obvious fixes
- Report format: summary + files changed + commands run + results
- All skill files (`.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md` and references) MUST be written in English. Korean is only allowed inside example user prompts or output templates that are explicitly user-facing
